You can also wrap your hands in a warm clothes to relax the joint. Make sure your hands are warm. I found that if you grip the inker to hard your hand will start to shake... so stay loose.<br>
<br>
If worse comes to worse, get someone else to ink for you. Teach some how to do it right, let them practice and then let them do it.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=wsl101>wsl101</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(10/26/02 4:09:34 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4478.topic&index=2>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.fhl-frisco.com/nate/ilovewsl2.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: inking (physical problems!?!?)</span><hr size=1> a lot of it is practice, my hands used to shake a lot, but ive been inking for a while and now they dont shake at all <p>---------------------------<br><font size=-2><a href="http://www.fhl-frisco.com/nate/index.html" target="_blank">The Art of Nathan Faubion</a><br><a href="http://pub57.ezboard.com/bchristianotaku">Association of Christian Otaku</a><br><a href="http://www.outcaststudios.com">Outcast Studios</a><br>Yvan eht <a href="http://pub90.ezboard.com/bkeepingthisfolderontop">kutoffed</a><br><a href="http://www.junkmunkies.com" underline="no">J U N K M U N K I E S</a></font><font style="display: none;"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=wizzurd@polykarbonbbs>Wizzurd</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Pre-Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(10/27/02 4:55:23 am)</fon