<br>
I noticed that the more careful and slower you trace your pencil line, the bigger the risk of making an error because of a little shake in the hand. That's probably because your hand muscles then tend to tense up. Sometimes lines come out better if you do them in a bit of a loose way, but still watching carefully as you go. It may sound a bit messy, but the keyword I'm looking for is: Smooth...at least, that's what I think...keep everything relaxed...Also, your lineart might even come to live, a little bit more...<br>
